FBIS3-52800 "drnes006_a_94002" FBIS-NES-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 ARAB AFRICA Algeria Six Civilians Killed in Last Week LD0801225694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 GMT 8 Jan 94 LD0801225694 Algiers Radio Algiers Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Regarding the security situation, Mohamed Belahcen, an official responsible for religious affairs in Ain Defla Province, was assassinated yesterday after the Friday prayers. The victim was 62 years old and was the imam of the Ghinali mosque in Medea. Six civilians were assassinated last week in El Tarf, Oum El Bouaghi, and Mostaganem provinces. In El Tarf Province, three militants of the FLN [National Liberation Front] were assassinated with knives on the night of 2 January after the hunting rifles in their possession were taken from them. In Oum El Bouaghi Province, the first deputy chairman of the executive authority of the (Ouled Hamda) municipality was assassinated the day before yesterday. Also the day before yesterday, in Mostaganem Province a retired health service employee was assassinated at the exit of the mosque in the town of Mostaganem. Meanwhile the security authorities said that they had killed four members of armed gangs and had arrested four others in the center and east of the country.
